Subject: [PATCH] feat(traceability): add responsive CompanyDetailSurface +
 real trace_id persistence

- New CompanyDetailSurface component: single responsive quick-look
  (mobile bottom sheet / tablet overlay / desktop slide-over) for the
  Companies page, with focus trap, Escape close, scroll lock, and
  loading/empty/error states. Wired into app/companies/page.tsx as a
  glance-and-quick-approve layer; /companies/[id] left untouched as the
  canonical deep-audit view.
- lib/stateMachine.ts: adapter mapping legacy free-form status strings
  to the strict IDLE/THINKING/EXECUTING/AWAITING_APPROVAL/BLOCKED/COMPLETE
  machine, with an unmapped-status fallback surfaced in the UI.
- lib/useBreakpoint.ts, lib/useOverlayA11y.ts: shared, reusable hooks
  (not one-off to this component) for the responsive switch and the
  overlay accessibility contract.
- Schema: additive trace_id TEXT column on activity_events and
  approvals via the existing ensureColumn() migration helper (PRAGMA
  check + ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN only, no table recreation). One-time
  idempotent backfill sets trace_id='legacy_migration' on pre-existing
  rows.
- Trace generation centralized at every real insertion point: lib/db.ts
  (saveActivityEvent, saveApproval, finalizeApprovedResult) and the
  worker's direct SQLite writes (execution_worker.py record_event +
  commit_result's approvals insert, supervisor_router.py record_event),
  via a shared trc_<12-hex> id format. No worker control-flow, Harness,
  or PolicyGate changes.
- CompanyDetailSurface now renders the real trace_id (with a neutral
  'Legacy' chip for backfilled rows) instead of the previous synthetic
  evt_#### placeholder, on both the activity feed and approval cards.
- Minor hygiene: __pycache__/*.pyc added to .gitignore.

Verified: eslint clean, production build green, python3 -m py_compile
clean on both worker files, and an end-to-end migration smoke test
against a simulated pre-migration SQLite DB confirmed the column is
added and legacy rows are backfilled without data loss.
